[[Image:Dock 7-2-2007 7-41-05 AM.jpg|thumb|Lighthouse and docks, Port Rowan, ON]]
'''Port Rowan''' is a town in [[Norfolk County, Ontario]] on [[Lake Erie]], adjacent to [[Long Point, Ontario|Long Point]]. This lakeside community has a population of less than 1000 people and sports a number of [[Small business|traditional small business]]es in addition to a growing retirement population.  Every [[Labor Day]] weekend, the town throws its annual Bayfest.

==History==

Key buildings, including John Backhouse`s mill, that date back to the 18th century, remain in existence today.<ref name=ForgottenSouthCoast>
{{cite news 
| url         = http://books.google.ca/books?id=y-6Rk89mj0IC&pg=PA88&dq=%22Port+Rowan%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MQ-wUOzvF8e3ywH1joGYDw&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=%22Port%20Rowan%22&f=false
| title       = The Lake Erie Shore: Ontario's Forgotten South Coast
| publisher   = [[Dundurn Group|Dundurn]]
| author      = Ron Brown
